.TH DYNOMITED 8 "2026-05-19" "v0.0.1"
.SH NAME
dynomited - a generic dynamo implementation for different key/value storage engines (Rust port).
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B Dynomited
is a thin, distributed Dynamo layer for different storage engines and protocols. Dynomite provides sharding and multi-data center replication. It has a shared nothing architecture with no single point of failure (SPOF) that delivers high availability (HA) even when a server, rack or entire data center goes offline.
.PP
Redis is currently the primary backend and protocol supported by Dynomite, while support for Memcached is partially implemented.
.PP
Dynomite provides the following functionality:
.IP \[bu]
Linear scalability
.IP \[bu]
High availability (HA)
.IP \[bu]
Shared nothing architecture with symmetric nodes
.IP \[bu]
Multi-data center (DC) replication
.IP \[bu]
Data replication and sharding
.IP \[bu]
Support for any Redis client plus a specialized Dyno client for Java
.IP \[bu]
Reduced connections to and lower connection overhead on backend storage engines via persistent connections
.IP \[bu]
Observability via easily accessible statistics
.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBdynomited\fR [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fB\-V\fR|\fB\-\-version\fR] [\fB\-t\fR|\fB\-\-test\-conf\fR] [\fB\-d\fR|\fB\-\-daemonize\fR] [\fB\-D\fR|\fB\-\-describe\-stats\fR] [\fB\-v\fR|\fB\-\-verbosity\fR] [\fB\-o\fR|\fB\-\-output\fR] [\fB\-c\fR|\fB\-\-conf\-file\fR] [\fB\-p\fR|\fB\-\-pid\-file\fR] [\fB\-x\fR|\fB\-\-admin\-operation\fR] [\fB\-m\fR|\fB\-\-mbuf\-size\fR] [\fB\-M\fR|\fB\-\-max\-msgs\fR] [\fB\-g\fR|\fB\-\-gossip\fR] 

.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Show the help banner and exit (sets [`Self::show_version`])
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Show the version banner and exit
.TP
\fB\-t\fR, \fB\-\-test\-conf\fR
Validate the configuration file and exit
.TP
\fB\-d\fR, \fB\-\-daemonize\fR
Daemonize: fork twice, become a session leader, redirect stdio to /dev/null
.TP
\fB\-D\fR, \fB\-\-describe\-stats\fR
Print the stats description and exit
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbosity\fR \fI<N>\fR [default: 5]
Numeric verbosity. Values outside `0..=11` are rejected
.TP
\fB\-o\fR, \fB\-\-output\fR \fI<FILE>\fR
Path to the log output file. `None` keeps logs on standard error
.TP
\fB\-c\fR, \fB\-\-conf\-file\fR \fI<FILE>\fR [default: conf/dynomite.yml]
Path to the YAML configuration file
.TP
\fB\-p\fR, \fB\-\-pid\-file\fR \fI<FILE>\fR
Path to the pid file. `None` disables the pid file
.TP
\fB\-x\fR, \fB\-\-admin\-operation\fR \fI<N>\fR [default: 0]
Admin operation flag. `0` means "no admin override"
.TP
\fB\-m\fR, \fB\-\-mbuf\-size\fR \fI<N>\fR
Deprecated mbuf chunk size override
.TP
\fB\-M\fR, \fB\-\-max\-msgs\fR \fI<N>\fR
Deprecated maximum allocated messages override
.TP
\fB\-g\fR, \fB\-\-gossip\fR
Force\-enable gossip regardless of the YAML setting

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR memcached (8),
.BR valkey-server (1)
